               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-340-person2355">
                  JAMES 
                  GILLESPIE
               <interp inst="t18310630-340-person2355" type="surname" value="GILLESPIE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-340-person2355" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-340-person2355" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman at the east-cellar of the London-docks. On the afternoon of the 25th of June I came out of the cellar, and saw the prisoners near a pipe of wine on the quay; the pipes had been set up to be repaired - Labay had a spile in his hand, ready to put into a hole which had been bored in the cask; Brenan was holding a bottle to catch the wine which was running out; when the bottle was full Lahay put the spile in - Brenan passed between me and Lahay, and put the bottle down between two casks; it contains about three quarters of a pint of port wine - I went to the gate, and reported them.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. STURGEON. Q.How long have you been a watchman there? A.Seven years - the prisoners had no business to taste wine.</p>
               <p>Lahay's Defence. There were other coopers there - I<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183106300147"></xptr>was gathering up my tools, and was some distance from the cask; this man has had a prejudice against me ever since last summer.</p>
               <p>Brenan's Defence. I know nothing of it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-340-person2356">
                  JAMES 
                  GILLESPIE
               <interp inst="t18310630-340-person2356" type="surname" value="GILLESPIE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-340-person2356" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-340-person2356" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoners were the only men near the cask.</p>
               <p>The prisoners received an excellent character.</p>
               <p>LAHAY - <rs id="t18310630-340-verdict1792" type="verdictDescription">
